 i. Free association: Clients express their thoughts and feelings spontaneously, allowing the therapist to identify recurring patterns and unconscious conflicts.
ii. Dream analysis: Therapists help clients explore the symbolic meaning of their dreams, uncovering unconscious desires and fears.
iii. Transference interpretation: Therapists analyze clients' emotional reactions and projections towards them, revealing unresolved issues from past relationships.
iv. Working through: Clients and therapists collaboratively process and integrate insights gained during therapy, promoting lasting change and personal growth.
v. Defense mechanisms: Therapists identify and address clients' unconscious strategies to avoid or cope with emotional pain, fostering self-awareness and emotional resilience